14	<section class="job-content imt-5 ipy-3 ipx-5 bg-it-white box-shadow-medium border-radius-large-md text-it-black" data-jobs--jd-scroll-target="jobContent">\r\n<div class="imy-3 paragraph">\r\n<h4>3 L&yacute; do để gia nhập c&ocirc;ng ty</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Attractive salary package and valuable benefits</li>\r\n<li>Get the opportunity to access global L&amp;D programs</li>\r\n<li>Hybrid and flexible working environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>M&ocirc; tả c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<h3>BUSINESS UNIT</h3>\r\n<p>HRS' Product Management department is a critical function in driving the success of the company's Lodging-as-a-Service (LaaS), Meeting-as-a-Service (MaaS) and Workforce-as-a-Service (WaaS) platform offerings. The department collaborates with cross-functional teams to define the product vision, roadmap, and strategy, and prioritizes features using analytics and data to meet business goals and deliver an exceptional experience for stakeholders. The teams in the Product Management department at HRS own the program backlog, define product increments and releases, and are responsible for the product vision, roadmap, pricing, licensing, and ROI.</p>\r\n<p>As a Product Manager on the travel tech team, you will play a central role in shaping the future of corporate travel. The travel tech team is responsible for the end-to-end customer experience of travelers, agents, and meeting planners through various online tools and APIs. You will work closely with design, engineering, sales, and marketing to define and build comprehensive solutions that enable corporate travelers at scale and unlock revenue opportunities.</p>\r\n<p><strong>CHALLENGE:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Build consumer-grade products that ensure friction-free experiences for our travelers throughout their entire trip, from searching to post-booking.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Work with our ecosystem partners to help them understand how our solutions create impact for their business, demonstrate that value through key business metrics, and show them how to improve that value over time.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Identify new product opportunities and drive a comprehensive roadmap informed by data analysis, qualitative research, customer feedback, and market/technology trends.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate externally with other ecosystem partners to develop custom, scalable integrations that align with their unique needs while supporting our mission and objectives.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Demonstrate a strong familiarity with developing external APIs and the ability to build within a partner's existing ecosystem, enhancing their overall experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Work in a dynamic, fast-paced environment where ambiguity is constant, exercising autonomy to drive product innovation and make strategic decisions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Apply common decision-making frameworks to evaluate opportunities and risks, drafting proposals through narrative/PRQs to communicate and guide these decisions.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Develop a long-term vision and product strategy aligned with our objectives, communicating effectively with senior leaders internally and externally to get buy-in and align teams towards executing the strategy.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Y&ecirc;u cầu c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Outcomes-driven with a bias for action and undaunted by multiple dependencies, both internal and external.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>At least 4+ years of product management experience in a software product, preferably within SaaS, marketplace, or e-commerce industry.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>An analytical, metrics-based approach to identifying, sizing, and solving problems, with excellent skills in identifying and prioritizing high-impact initiatives.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Strong written and verbal communication skills with the ability to articulate customer problems and drive alignment with cross-functional teams and leadership.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>An experimentation mindset to come up with hypotheses, test them quickly, and ship features globally.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Equally comfortable diving into technical details with an engineer, iterating on a Figma with a designer, or breaking down a funnel with a data analyst.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>A scrappy, get-things-done attitude to make your product and team successful, whether that means writing a QA plan or investigating the root cause of a customer support ticket.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with SQL, and data visualization tools such as MicroStrategy/Tableau for product analysis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Tại sao bạn sẽ y&ecirc;u th&iacute;ch l&agrave;m việc tại đ&acirc;y</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Full salary and benefits</strong> as an official employee <strong>on probation</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Hybrid working</strong> model.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Open and flat environment</strong>, highly appreciate your idea and constantly supporting your skill development.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Innovative and international learning and development program</strong>, we dedicate to supporting employees&rsquo; growth and development of skills.</li>\r\n<li>Challenging products with <strong>onsite opportunities in Europe</strong> (Germany, Australia, Poland, etc.).</li>\r\n<li><strong>13th-month salary &amp; short-term incentives</strong>: we offer incentives as defined by the company&rsquo;s success in the previous year.</li>\r\n<li>15+ annual leaves per year.</li>\r\n<li>Full healthcare compliance.</li>\r\n<li>Premium healthcare for employees.</li>\r\n<li>Gifts for every special occasion.</li>\r\n<li>Supportive working conditions: Laptop, MS Surface Hub.</li>\r\n<li>Free and unlimited snacks, tea, coffee, and by-choice request.</li>\r\n<li>Premium company trip &amp; business traveling programs and other exciting activities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Note: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Thanks for your interest!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>	t	1,500 - 2,500 USD	Product Manager (Travel Tech)	2025-02-22 21:58:54.386	Remote	3
26	<section class="job-content imt-5 ipy-3 ipx-5 bg-it-white box-shadow-medium border-radius-large-md text-it-black" data-jobs--jd-scroll-target="jobContent">\r\n<div class="imy-3 paragraph">\r\n<h4>3 L&yacute; do để gia nhập c&ocirc;ng ty</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Very competitive remuneration package</li>\r\n<li>Build products for millions of users in Australia</li>\r\n<li>Hybrid and flexible working environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>M&ocirc; tả c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<p><em><strong>By applying for the above position, you accept and agree that your personal data and any information stated in the attached curriculum vitae (CV) will be used and processed by ITViec and NAB Vietnam for recruitment purposes. The storage and processing of such information will comply with the applicable laws of Vietnam, and the policies and procedures of ITViec and NAB Vietnam regarding personal data, as amended from time to time.</strong></em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Your Job Responsibilities</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lead the technical direction-setting for key business outcomes &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Deliver an end-to-end technical outcome across one or more banking domains. They identify service impacts. They understand how new and existing target states will be consumed to deliver and initiative. They work to shape and sequence initiative features on service backlogs.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Provide technical direction and consultation to the architecture team, across the technology lifecycle, creating and maintaining the Target State Architecture for each capability within the domain and mapping all components to the assest management system.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Align application roadmap to NAB technology strategy and architectural principles/patterns.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Perform architecture optimization, scaled modeling, various forms of walkthroughs design reviews&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Drive the service feature backlog grooming and raises features, epics and stories as suited for delivery and providing architecture input into the prioritization of backlog items. Ensure capabilities external to the service are also identified a dependencies where appropriate.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Create impact analysis of functional and non-functional requirements and constraints on the business roadmap in the current business and technology environment including the regulatory impacts and risks.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Make the document architectural decisions to satisfy regulatory and compliance requirements for the domain.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Validate design artifacts for completeness, ensuring testability to enable effective change management of assessments within the domain.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Support &ldquo;You build it, you run it&rdquo; by participating in service production releases.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Y&ecirc;u cầu c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Experience of <strong>10+ years in Technology generally.&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li>Experience of<strong> 5+ years in end-to-end solution architecture design.&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li>Experience driving <strong>end-to-end solutions in complex organisations</strong> with regulatory and legacy constraints.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Strong business acumen and engagement skills</strong> to influence business strategy to help shape, triage, prioritize business outcomes and develop roadmaps for the business unit/domains.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Financial services experience is essential.</strong><strong> </strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Commercial / Business Lending experience </strong>highly desirable. Experience in specialised finance, in particular Leasing / Equipment Finance is beneficial, as is any experience in programs of legacy transformation work.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Ability to lead and maintain backlog of business outcomes portfolio view of the business domain.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in working in a scale agile structure to help coordinate work to a persistent team of solution architects.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Proven experience in strong business engagement, and influencing skills with the ability to navigate complex topics with fact-based analysis.&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Understand the trade-off involved in technology change</strong> while simultaneously delivering <strong>business benefits.&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li>Require commercial acumen, business alignment, and ability to negotiate.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Degree in Computer Science/information system or equivalent technical qualification.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Architecture or technology-related certifications/cloud will be an advantage.&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li>Business acumen in the banking / financial; services industry will be an advantage.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Tại sao bạn sẽ y&ecirc;u th&iacute;ch l&agrave;m việc tại đ&acirc;y</h4>\r\n<p><strong>1. Generous compensation and benefit package</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Attractive salary and benefits &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>20-day annual leave and 7-day sick leave, etc. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>13th month salary and Annual Performance Bonus &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Premium healthcare for yourself and family members &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>2. Exciting career and development opportunities </strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Large scale products with modern technologies in banking domain &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Clear roadmap for career advancement in both technical and leadership pathways &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Sponsored certificates in both IT and banking/finance &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Premium accounts on Udemy/A Cloud Guru/Coursera/LinkedIn, etc. &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>English learning with native teachers &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>3. Professional and engaging working environment</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hybrid working model and excellent work-life balance   &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Well-equipped &amp; modern Agile office with fully-stocked pantry  &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Annual company trip and events   &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br><strong>A DIVERSE AND INCLUSIVE WORKPLACE WORKS BETTER FOR EVERYONE</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NAB is a place where colleagues of all genders, sexualities and ages, carers and colleagues with disability, and colleagues from all cultures, races and religions have the opportunity to thrive, connect and grow.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><br><strong>If this excites you, let's have a chat over a cup of coffee!</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>	t	You'll love it	Solution Architect	2025-02-22 22:37:56.948	Hybrid	7
16	<section class="job-content imt-5 ipy-3 ipx-5 bg-it-white box-shadow-medium border-radius-large-md text-it-black" data-jobs--jd-scroll-target="jobContent">\r\n<div class="imy-3 paragraph">\r\n<h4>3 L&yacute; do để gia nhập c&ocirc;ng ty</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Attractive salary package and valuable benefits</li>\r\n<li>Get the opportunity to access global L&amp;D programs</li>\r\n<li>Hybrid and flexible working environment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>M&ocirc; tả c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<p><strong>BUSINESS UNIT</strong></p>\r\n<p>BPATech provides a platform for our corporate customers to automate their crew and workforce accommodation workflows. It connects both to customer and the internal HRS systems to heavily drive process automation. The BPA platform is offered as SaaS and built upon a modern tech stack (Dotnet, React, Azure, Kubernetes, SOA).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We are looking for a Team Lead who loves to build top notch SAAS application delivering an outstanding user experience for Travelers, Meeting Planners and Hotel Partners.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lead an engineering team of 9 members to develop and maintain excellent software products.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Proactively discuss and consult the Product Managers and other stakeholders at Head Quarter to ensure that the technical point of view is brought into consideration while planning and growing the products.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate with other people responsible for the relevant products to ensure that the technical solution is optimum and best fit to the latest cloud architecture.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Manage and support team members to become a highly performing engineering team.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Coach engineers to adopt best practices in software development lifecycle, such as Infrastructure as Code, Automated testing, Continuous Integration - Continuous Delivery/Deployment, etc.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Coach engineers to leverage generative Al tools such as GitHub Copilot, Amazon Code Whisperer, etc., to accelerate software delivery.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate across teams with regards to overarching technical concepts and practices.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in the full development cycle: design, development, QA, experimentation, analysis, and launch. You'll be reviewing code, writing design documents, giving feedback on product specs and mocks, and generally helping out wherever is needed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Y&ecirc;u cầu c&ocirc;ng việc</h4>\r\n<p>Experience: 5+ years of experience in programming software using C#, modern cloud software architecture, and related technologies.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Technology and Management Expertise:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>2+ years experience in technical leadership over high performing engineering teams.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Solid understanding of core software engineering concepts and API designs&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Experience implementing and running high-performing containerized applications at scale on Azure&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Significant experience in one or more general purpose programming languages (C#, Java, Go, Python,&hellip;)&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of and experience in working with agile methodologies&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Vision and Execution:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ability to implement and achieve a compelling vision for the future, with actionable plans to achieve long term objectives.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Strong accountability for meeting tactical objectives and commitments within the established methodological framework.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Experience in developing concepts and leading development execution of market-leading Saas product offerings.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Leadership and Communication:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Excellent leadership and coaching skills to guide and inspire the team.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Effective presentation and speaking skills and the ability to communicate with a wide range of different stakeholders&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Adaptability and Innovation:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ability to work within a fast-paced, evolving environment where products and solutions evolve quickly and need to be accurately integrated into customer/sales story lines as the solutions evolve. Embrace changes and drive innovation. Skilled in working within a matrix organization and in forwarding, building momentum for and successfully driving the competition of strategic initiatives that impact a total organization and company.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Problem-solving and Creativity:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Strong problem-solving skills and creativity to develop new possibilities and processes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Personal Attributes:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Empathy, authenticity, integrity, commitment, resilience, and respect in dealing with all stakeholders.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Language Skills:&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluency in English, spoken and written.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Tại sao bạn sẽ y&ecirc;u th&iacute;ch l&agrave;m việc tại đ&acirc;y</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Full salary and benefits</strong> as an official employee <strong>on probation</strong>.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Hybrid working</strong> model.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Open and flat environment</strong>, highly appreciate your idea and constantly supporting your skill development.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Innovative and international learning and development program</strong>, we dedicate to supporting employees&rsquo; growth and development of skills.</li>\r\n<li>Challenging products with <strong>onsite opportunities in Europe</strong> (Germany, Australia, Poland, etc.).</li>\r\n<li><strong>13th-month salary &amp; short-term incentives</strong>: we offer incentives as defined by the company&rsquo;s success in the previous year.</li>\r\n<li>15+ annual leaves per year.</li>\r\n<li>Full healthcare compliance.</li>\r\n<li>Premium healthcare for employees.</li>\r\n<li>Gifts for every special occasion.</li>\r\n<li>Supportive working conditions: Laptop, MS Surface Hub.</li>\r\n<li>Free and unlimited snacks, tea, coffee, and by-choice request.</li>\r\n<li>Premium company trip &amp; business traveling programs and other exciting activities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Note: Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. Thanks for your interest!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>	t	3,000 - 3,200 USD	Engineering Team Lead (.NET)	2025-02-22 22:01:49.397	Hybrid	3
