2	<div class="imy-3 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Top 3 reasons to join us</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Global Exposure</li>\r\n<li>Fast Track Career</li>\r\n<li>Diversified Jobs &amp; Technologies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="imy-5 paragraph">\r\n<h4>Job description</h4>\r\n<p><strong>About us</strong></p>\r\n<p>A subsidiary of the FPT Group, FPT Software is known as a leading global information technology service provider headquartered in Vietnam. With over 30,000 employees working in 83 offices across 30 countries on five continents, FPT Software consistently delivers the best solutions to more than 1000 clients, including 100 Fortune 500 companies. Placing human resources as the cornerstone of its achievements, employee experience is our top priority in continually creating an innovative, open, and enjoyable work environment for every member.</p>\r\n<p>In 2023, FPT Software officially made its mark on the global billion-dollar company list. This is evidence of the talent and efforts of multiple generations of employees at FPT Software.</p>\r\n<p>Why not explore your potential and embark on a brilliant journey with us?</p>\r\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>The Business Analyst (BA) is responsible for:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Supporting and leading any new large/complex opportunities from sales team at assessment and proposal phases.</li>\r\n<li>Provide initial and comprehensive analysis direction for technical design and business requirement of new projects.</li>\r\n<li>Support presentation of new solutions or services as advantages and benefits in pre-sales environment.</li>\r\n<li>Work closely with customers to understand their business processes and system requirements.</li>\r\n<li>Translate customer&rsquo;s requirements into software requirement specifications.</li>\r\n<li>Interact with the development team to make sure requirements are fully and correctly understood.</li>\r\n<li>Verify the system main functionalities to make sure they meet 